---
import TransformationPair from '../patterns/TransformationPair.astro';
---

<section id="about" class="py-[var(--spacing-section)] border-t border-slate-gray">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="explanatory-c-heading" data-animate="headline">
        Landmarks, <span class="italic-accent">not lookalikes.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
      <p class="font-body text-soft-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        A landmark is the building people use to give directions. "Turn left at the place with the mural." "Park across from the hand-painted sign." It's the building strangers go out of their way to find, the one they photograph and send to friends who've never been to the neighborhood. A landmark signals to the whole block that someone cares about this corner. People notice that. They trust it. They walk in.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-soft-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        A lookalike signals nothing. The vinyl banner that could hang on any storefront in any city. The template mural that looks the same in Richmond as it does in Denver. Your brain processes these the same way it processes a blank wall: as background. Nobody stops. Nobody asks about it. And nobody who owns one has ever been proud of it. The work on your building should be something you brag about, not something you settle for. It should mean something specific to you, so that when someone asks why it looks the way it does, you have a real answer.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        I paint landmarks. Murals built from real research into the people and places that matter to the project. Signs painted by hand with the kind of intention you can feel from across the street. Every color documented. Every element traceable to its source. Work that belongs to your building, your block, and your story, and could not be copied onto anyone else's wall.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
      <TransformationPair
        leftImage="/images/content-design/trolley-render.jpg"
        rightImage="/images/content-design/trolley-full.jpg"
        leftAlt="A generic building wall before mural work"
        rightAlt="The same building transformed into a landmark with a hand-painted mural"
        leftLabel="Before"
        rightLabel="After"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .explanatory-c-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    color: var(--color-titanium-white);
    font-size: var(--text-fluid-5xl);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
</style>
